    <h1> Documentation
     for ARTS version @VERSION@</h1>

    <p>
      This page gives an overview of the documentation that comes
      inside the ARTS package.

    <h2> ARTS User Guide (AUG)</h2>

    <p>
      This should become the comprehensive manual for ARTS, both for
      users and developers. Should it become too large we will split
      it at some point in the future. Here you can:

    <ul>
      <li>
	Look at the <a href="uguide/uguide.ps"> Postscript version</a>.
      <li>
	Look at the <a href="uguide/uguide_pdf.pdf"> Pdf version</a>.
    </ul>

    <p>
      I also tried to convert the document to html using latex2html,
      but this did not yield satisfactory results. Figures and
      equations did not show up at all. Also, the redifined sectioning
      commands (levela, etc.) seem to confuse the translator. Should
      anybody want to work on this, please go ahead! Otherwise, for
      now we are stuck with the printable version.


    <h2> Automatic source code documentation with Doxygen</h2>

    <p>
      We use the doxygen program to extract documentation from comments
      inside the source code. See the development section in the user
      guide for information on how this is done. Here is the result as:

    <ul>
      <li>
	<a href="doxygen/html/index.html"> HTML document</a>.
<!--  <li> -->
<!-- 	<a href="doxygen/latex/refman.ps"> Postscript file</a> (generated -->
<!-- 	from a LaTeX source). -->
    </ul>

    <p>
      For convenience, we have also added emacs macros that can be
      used to automatically insert documentation headers. A
      description can be found 	
      <a href="emacs/doxygen_toc.html"> here</a>. These macros were
      originally written by <a href="mailto:tree@basistech.com"> Tom
      Emerson</a>, and slightly adapted for ARTS.

    
    <h2> Example ARTS control files</h2>

    <p>
      The package contains everything that you need to run these
      examples. Currently they are:

    <ul>
      <li>
	<a href="examples/auto_example1.arts"> auto_example1.arts</a> (calculates
	absorption coefficients).
      <li>
	<a href="examples/cont.arts"> cont.arts</a> (shows how to use continua).
      <li>
	<a href="examples/auto_full.arts"> auto_full.arts</a> (an end-to-end
	job).
    </ul>

